HEADWORD: Telegony
<hw>Te*leg"o*ny</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>th^le</grk> far + root of Gr. <?/ to be born.]</ety>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The supposed influence of a father upon
offspring subsequent to his own, begotten of the same mother by another
father.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Te*leg"o*nous</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

